fullDescription:
Client:

- audit and tax consulting

​

Job description:

- being the bridge between our technology teams and the client;
- gathering and mapping business requirements, processes and objectives;
- analyzing the design of technical systems and business models;
- communicate with client about development of necessary system modifications to satisfy business needs;
- preparing reports, presentations on application development and implementation;
- creating functional specifications and user stories;
- participating on project management activities;
- guidance and mentoring of junior team members.

​

Requirements:

- PowerPoint, Excel experience (Visio, Aris - advantage);
- knowledge of agile methodologies;
- tracking tolls as Jira, Azure DevOps (nice to have);
- experience with mapping and implementation of processes is highly preferable;
- experience with testing, UX/UI design and prototyping (by using Figma) would be considered as advantage;
- previous experience with a business analyst role for at least 2,5 years.
- Active knowledge of the German language (minimum B2) is a plus.
- university degree (IT, technical or business background);
- strong analytical mindset and sharp logical thinking;
- previous experience from consulting company (nice to have);
- creative approach to problem solving;
- ability to pick up new concepts and technologies;
- attention to detail

​

Benefits:

- hybrid working policy: flexible work time and home office;
- regular salary increase and performance bonus;
- meal contribution and Multi-sport card;
- we appreciate your extra work, every minute counts (paid overtimes);
- sick days and additional days off for Christmas;
- cafeteria system;
- opportunity to develop your career in a team of international experts;
- internal learning platform and external trainings;
- “Be well, work well program” - human dynamic advisory, workshops for mental health topics, social events and activities, vouchers for activities;
